{"id": "7af43df2", "type": "grammar_rule", "kodava": "`avala noatiyand ikkathe!`", "devanagari": "", "english": "`ava'k noatiyand ikkathe!` (FINAL.md line 2038 — \"Don't keep staring at her!\")", "explanation": "\"Staring at her\" requires accusative case (direct object), not dative. Equivalent to Kannada: **avalannu** nodkond irabeda (accusative ✓) NOT: avalige nodkond irabeda (dative ✗) `ava'k` = dative (to her / for her benefit) — wrong for staring `avala` = accusative (her, direct object) — correct", "confidence": "verified", "source": "kodava_corrections.md", "tags": ["correction"]}
